Cell.Text: So you're the Dragonborn I've been hearing so much about.
G|Close the door, then we can talk.
G|Not here. Follow me.
The Greybeards seem to think you're the Dragonborn. I hope they're right.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroTopic: What do you want?

Cell.Text: Surprised? I guess I'm getting pretty good at my harmless innkeeper act.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroA1: You're the one who took the horn?

Cell.Text: [S] You can't be too careful. Thalmor spies are everywhere.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroA2: What's with all the cloak and dagger?

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> I didn't go to all this trouble on a whim. I needed to make sure it wasn't a Thalmor trap.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroB1: What do you want with me?

Cell.Text: [S] It was the only way I could make sure it wasn't a Thalmor trap.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroB2: You'd better have a good reason for dragging me here.

Cell.Text: [S] S|<<Shared>> I'm not your enemy. I already gave you the horn. I'm actually trying to help you. I just need you to listen to what I have to say.
You ready to hear me out?

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveTopic: I just came here for the horn.

Cell.Text: Like I said in my note, I've heard that you might be Dragonborn.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveA1: Go on. I'm listening.

Cell.Text: I'll explain what I want when I want, got it? You'd already be dead if I didn't like the look of you when you walked in here. | But I had to know if the rumors about you were true...

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveA2: You'd better start explaining. Fast.

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> I shouldn't let you walk out of here, knowing what you know. But I guess even my paranoia has its limits. | You know where to find me when you change your mind. Because you will. You have to.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveA3: I don't have time for this.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> I'm part of group that's been looking for you... well, someone like you, for a very long time. | If you really are Dragonborn, that is. Before I tell you any more, I need to make sure I can trust you.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveB1

Cell.Text: S|If you don't trust me, you were a fool to walk in here in the first place.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveC1: How do I know I can trust you?

Cell.Text: [S] S|<<Shared>> We remember what most don't - that the Dragonborn is the ultimate dragonslayer. | You're the only one that can kill a dragon permanently by devouring its soul.
[S] <<Shared>> We remember what most don't - that the Dragonborn is the ultimate dragonslayer. | You're the only one that can kill a dragon permanently by devouring its soul.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveC3Dragonborn: Why are you looking for a Dragonborn?

Cell.Text: Dragons aren't just coming back, they're coming back to life. | They weren't gone somewhere for all these years. They were dead, killed off centuries ago by my predecessors. | Now something's happening to bring them back to life. And I need you to help me stop it.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveD1: So what's the part you're not telling me.

Cell.Text: [S] I know they are. I've visited their ancient burial mounds and found them empty. | And I've figured out where the next one will come back to life. | We're going to go there, and you're going to kill that dragon. If we succeed, I'll tell you anything you want to know.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusive2A2: What makes you think dragons are coming back to life?

Cell.Text: Ha. A few years ago, I said almost the same thing to a colleague of mine. Well, it turned out he was right and I was wrong.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusive2A1: Do you know how crazy this sounds?

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> Kynesgrove. There's an ancient dragon burial near there. If we can get there before it happens, maybe we'll learn how to stop it.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveEndTopic: So where are we headed?

Cell.Text: I hope you're just playing dumb. I'm the one who left the note in Ustengrav.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroA3: Sorry, I'm supposed to be meeting someone here.

Cell.Text: Good. The whole point of being in hiding is to appear to be someone you're not.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroA3A1: I was expecting someone... taller.

Cell.Text: [S] G|I think you're looking for this.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroA0: What of it?

Cell.Text: I hope so. But you'll forgive me if I don't assume that something's true just because the Greybeards say so. | I just handed you the Horn of Jurgen Windcaller. Does that make me Dragonborn, too?

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroA4: The Greybeards are right. I am Dragonborn.

Cell.Text: [S] Good. Good. Now we won't have to spend time searching for it. | We should get moving. There's no time to waste.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroEndA1: I know that mound - high on the hill east of Kynesgrove.

Cell.Text: G|I need to get into my traveling gear. Give me a minute and I'll be ready.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroEndA2: Let's go kill a dragon.

Cell.Text: G|I can't wait around for you to make up your mind. I'll meet you at Kynesgrove. Don't waste time getting there.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroEndA3: Hold on. I'm not ready to go yet.

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> I shouldn't let you walk out of here, knowing what you know. But I guess even my paranoia has its limits. | You know where to find me when you change your mind. Because you will. You have to.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveC5: I don't need to prove anything to you. I'm done here.

Cell.Text: [S] And now you have it. No harm done. | I knew the Greybeards would send you for the horn if they thought you were Dragonborn. | Taking it was the only way I could be sure this wasn't a Thalmor trap.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroB3: I just came here for the horn.

Cell.Text: Yes. We're very old enemies. And if my suspicions are correct, they might have something to do with the dragons returning. | But that isn't important right now. What is important is that you might be Dragonborn.
You said you're in hiding? From who?

[S] The Thalmor. We're very old enemies. And if my suspicions are correct, they might have something to do with the dragons returning. | But that isn't important right now. What is important is that you might be Dragonborn.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelpineIntroExclusiveC4ThalmorTopic: You said the Thalmor are after you?

Cell.Text: Something's happening to bring the dragons back to life. And I need you to help me stop it.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusive2EntryTopic: You want me to kill a dragon for you?

Cell.Text: [S] I knew the Greybeards would send you there if they thought you were Dragonborn. They're nothing if not traditionalists. | When you showed up here, I knew you were the one the Greybeards sent, and not some Thalmor plant.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelpineIntroExclusiveC2Horn: Why did you take the horn from Ustengrav?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> I'm part of group that's been looking for you... well, someone like you, for a very long time. | If you really are Dragonborn, that is. Before I tell you any more, I need to make sure I can trust you.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelpineIntroExclusiveDragonbornEntryTopic

Cell.Text: S|<<Shared>> You should know. You got the map for me. The Dragonstone you got for Farengar, remember?
S|You should know. You got the map for me from Bleak Falls Barrow.

<<Shared>> The Dragonstone is a map of ancient dragon burial sites. I've looked at which ones are now empty. The pattern is pretty clear. | It seems to be spreading from the southeast, down in the Jeralls near Riften. The one at Kynesgrove is next if the pattern holds.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusive2A3: How did you figure all this out?

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> So you were paying attention. I arranged to have Farengar recover the dragonstone for me. | It's what I do. I make things happen from behind the scenes. After all, here you are.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusive2A2A1: Right. You were at Dragonsreach when I gave it to him.

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> I didn't go to all this trouble on a whim. I needed to make sure it wasn't a Thalmor trap.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroA3A2: Here I am. What do you want?

Cell.Text: Can you do it? Can you devour a dragon's soul?

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusiveC3A1: What of it?

Cell.Text: Good. And you'll have a chance to prove it to me soon enough.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroDragonbornA1: Yes, that's how I first learned I was Dragonborn.

Cell.Text: This is no time to play the reluctant hero. You either are or aren't Dragonborn. | But I'll see for myself soon enough.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroDragonbornA2: I absorb some kind of power from dragons. That's all I can say.

Cell.Text: You're wrong. It is my business. You may be the only one that can stop these dragons. | But you'll understand that soon enough.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroDragonbornA3: That's none of your business.

Cell.Text: Yes. It shows ancient dragon burial sites. I've looked at which ones are now empty. The pattern is pretty clear. | It seems to be spreading from the southeast, starting in the Jeralls near Riften. The one near Kynesgrove is next if the pattern holds.

Node.Caption: MQ106DelphineIntroExclusive2A2A2: The Dragonstone was some kind of map?
